

	 
      From  urlLink Wordsmith :  philodox (FIL-uh-doks) noun     Someone who loves his or her own opinion; a dogmatic person.  [From Greek philodoxos, from philo- (love) + doxa (glory, opinion). Ultimately from Indo-European root dek- (to take or accept) that's also the root of words such as paradox, orthodox, doctor, disciple, discipline, doctrine, dogma, decorate, dignity, and disdain.]   Aren't we all a little philodox from time to time?  
     
    
